@page "/about"
@using MudBlazor

<PageTitle>About - QSMPDLE</PageTitle>

<WebPage>

    <h2>
        About the Game
    </h2>

    <p class="info">
        A daily guessing game dedicated to the characters of QSMP2.
    </p>

    <MudAlert Severity="Severity.Info" Dense="true" Variant="Variant.Outlined" Class="mb-6">
        This is an unofficial fan project and is not affiliated with QSMP or its creators.
    </MudAlert>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <h3>
            So, what is it?
        </h3>

        <p>
            QSMPDLE is a character guessing game inspired by Wordle and similar daily puzzle games.
        </p>

        <p>
            Every day, players are challenged to identify a QSMP character using a series
            of clues and comparisons. Each guess helps narrow down the possibilities until
            the correct answer is found.
        </p>

        <p>
            Whether you're a casual viewer, a lore enthusiast, or someone who can recite
            an entire character arc from memory, the goal is simple:
        </p>

        <MudPaper Outlined="true" Class="quote-box pa-6 mt-4 w-75 mx-auto text-center">
            <strong>
                Guess the character before you run out of ideas.
            </strong>
        </MudPaper>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <h3>
            Why Was It Created?
        </h3>

        <p>
            Because QSMP has a huge cast of memorable characters, complicated lore,
            legendary moments, questionable decisions, emotional damage, and far more
            eggs than most stories reasonably require.
        </p>

        <p>
            It felt like the perfect setting for a guessing game.
        </p>

        <p>
            The project started as a small experiment and gradually evolved into a fully
            playable fan-made experience.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <h3>
            Features
        </h3>

        <ul>
            <li>Daily character challenges</li>
            <li>Practice mode</li>
            <li>Player statistics and streaks</li>
            <li>Character information and lore references</li>
            <li>Playable entirely in your browser</li>
            <li>No account required</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <h3>
            About The Project
        </h3>

        <p>
            QSMPDLE is developed and maintained by a single fan in their spare time.
        </p>

        <p>
            New features, visual improvements, bug fixes, and additional content are added
            whenever time, energy, and real life permit.
        </p>

        <p>
            If something breaks, there's a good chance the developer is already looking
            directly at the same bug wondering how it happened.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-3 text-center">

        <h3>
            One Last Thing
        </h3>

        <div class="story-box">

            <p>
                If you get today's character in one guess,
                congratulations.
            </p>

            <p>
                If it takes fifteen guesses,
                congratulations.
            </p>

            <p>
                If you spend twenty minutes staring at the screen before
                realizing you forgot an entire character existed,
                welcome to QSMP.
            </p>

        </div>

    </section>

</WebPage>

<style>
    .about-card {
        max-width: 850px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        border-radius: 24px;
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
        backdrop-filter: blur(16px);
    }

    .section-title {
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        font-weight: 700;
    }

    .about-card p {
        line-height: 1.8;
        opacity: .95;
    }

    .quote-box {
        border-radius: 16px;
    }

    .story-box {
        padding: 2rem;
        border-radius: 20px;
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
        border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    }

    .story-box p:last-child {
        margin-bottom: 0;
    }
</style>
